IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. INTEREST-RATE.

DATA DIVISION.
WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01 WS-CMD        PIC X(50).
01 WS-SCORE-TXT  PIC X(10).
01 WS-SCORE      PIC 9(3).

01 WS-BASE-RATE  PIC 9(2)V9 VALUE 7.0.
01 WS-PREMIUM    PIC 9(2)V9 VALUE 0.
01 WS-FINAL      PIC 9(3)V9.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
    ACCEPT WS-CMD FROM COMMAND-LINE
    MOVE FUNCTION NUMVAL(WS-CMD) TO WS-SCORE

    EVALUATE TRUE
        WHEN WS-SCORE >= 800 MOVE 1.5 TO WS-PREMIUM
        WHEN WS-SCORE >= 750 MOVE 2.0 TO WS-PREMIUM
        WHEN WS-SCORE >= 700 MOVE 3.0 TO WS-PREMIUM
        WHEN WS-SCORE >= 650 MOVE 4.5 TO WS-PREMIUM
        WHEN WS-SCORE >= 600 MOVE 6.0 TO WS-PREMIUM
        WHEN OTHER MOVE 8.0 TO WS-PREMIUM
    END-EVALUATE

    COMPUTE WS-FINAL = WS-BASE-RATE + WS-PREMIUM
    DISPLAY WS-FINAL
    STOP RUN.

